We try not to do that for important values. What's a good reason for having this configurable at the command line?

288:0-293:5
Fri Aug 12 17:02:32 2016 +0000
Author: Dan Austin <1079886@85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889>
Parent: dedd6d2d_c6de9838
UUID: dedd6d2d_d1b9f4bc
Bytes: 330
Basically convenience. When I'm writing up how to configure a build to use asan/coverage, it's easier to say "address this issue by setting ART_TARGET_SIZE_LIMIT" than "modify this makefile in this way" It's not a showstopper, but is easier to explain when building multiple targets that may/may not have this issue in the future.

